# {{BINARY_NAME}} {{VERSION}} ({{PLATFORM}})

HomeCore plugin fragment. Statically-linked musl binary — no glibc, no
OpenSSL, no system dependencies.

This archive only contains files under `homecore/plugins/{{BINARY_NAME}}/`.
Extract it on top of an existing core install — the `homecore/` directory
will merge cleanly without overwriting anything else.

## Layout

    homecore/
    └── plugins/
        └── {{BINARY_NAME}}/
            ├── bin/{{BINARY_NAME}}
            └── config/
                └── config.toml.example

## Install

Assuming you already extracted a `homecore-core-*` archive next to where
you want this plugin to land:

    cd <parent of homecore/>
    tar -xzf {{BINARY_NAME}}-{{VERSION}}-{{PLATFORM}}.tar.gz

Copy the example config and fill in your device-side credentials:

    cp homecore/plugins/{{BINARY_NAME}}/config/config.toml.example \
       homecore/plugins/{{BINARY_NAME}}/config/config.toml
    $EDITOR homecore/plugins/{{BINARY_NAME}}/config/config.toml

Then enable the plugin in your core's `homecore/config/homecore.toml`:

    [[plugins]]
    id      = "plugin.<short-name>"
    binary  = "plugins/{{BINARY_NAME}}/bin/{{BINARY_NAME}}"
    config  = "plugins/{{BINARY_NAME}}/config/config.toml"
    enabled = true

Restart core to spawn the plugin.

## Verifying this archive

    sha256sum -c {{BINARY_NAME}}-{{VERSION}}-{{PLATFORM}}.tar.gz.sha256

If verification fails, do not extract.

